  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Assistant",
  "description": "<p>The company seeks a reliable, meticulous, and knowledgeable Accounts Assistant to provide support to the financial department by managing daily accounting tasks. You will be part of a wider regional team, working to ensure accounts are maintained and cashflow is balanced with the ultimate goal of contributing to the company’s operational efficiency and success.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>·        Maintain financial recording in the ERP program</p><p>·        Perform general entry bookkeeping</p><p>·        Maintains general ledger accounts, reconciling accounts receivable and accounts payable details</p><p>·        Assist in the processing of balance sheets, income statements and other financial statements according to legal and company accounting and financial guidelines.</p><p>·        Assist Accountant in the preparation of monthly and yearly closing.</p><p>·        Submit GST on behalf of the company.</p><p>·        Manage cash flow, collections, and aging reports.</p><p>·        Analyse and reconcile bank statements and general ledgers</p><p>·        Inventory analysis.</p><p>·        Maintain regular communication with manager and other staff and assist as needed</p><p>·        Assist local auditors when required</p><p>·        Support ad-hoc tasks when required<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>·        Knowledge of Netsuite is a plus</p><p>·        Minimum with 1 year of Accounting or Bookkeeping experience - including experience managing A/R, A/P, and performing basic accounting functions.</p><p>·        Knowledge of basic bookkeeping or accounting principles.</p><p>·        Excellent organizational, time management, and problem-solving abilities.</p><p>·        Excellent interpersonal skills, professional appearance and demeanour.</p><p>·        Strong knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite including Word and Excel.</p>",
